oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Battle of Paris
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a drawing depicting the Battle of Paris. There are multiple soldiers holding guns, a horse, and a fallen soldier on the left. The writing says, "Skirmisher of King's Kentucky Battalion Confederate Cavalry in action. At Paris Tennessee March 11th 1862".
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Cavalry; Soldiers; Horses; Drawings
